  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT309-kilavi">parattaiyiṟ pirintu vanta kiḻavaṟkut tōḻi vāyil nērntatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">The confidante granting the door to HIM, who came after
          having separated from the other woman/courtesan. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT309">
          <l> kaiviṉai mākkaṭañ ceyviṉai muṭimār</l>
          <l> curumpuṇa malarnta vācaṅ kīḻppaṭa</l>
          <l> nīṭiṉa varampiṉ vāṭiya viṭiṉuṅ</l>
          <l> koṭiyarō nilampeyarn tuṟaivē meṉṉātu</l>
          <l> peyarttuṅ kaṭinta ceṟuviṟ pūkku</l>
          <l> niṉṉūr neyta laṉaiyēm peruma</l>
          <l> nīyemak kiṉṉā taṉapala ceyyiṉu</l>
          <l> niṉṉiṉ ṟamaital vallā māṟē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent2">Because we are not able to be content without you,</l>
          <l rend="indent5">even if you do to us many unkind [things],</l>
          <l>o great one, we [are] like the blue waterlily in your village,</l>
          <l rend="indent">flowering in the field, chased away [ever] again, without saying</l>
          <l rend="indent">“as for [these] cruel ones, we move away<note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> uṟai-tal </term> as an auxiliary adds the nuance of permanence: to go away once and for all.   </note> from [their] ground,”</l>
          <l rend="indent2">even if [they] let it fade on the long [field] borders,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">so that the fragrance gives way, flourished for bees to eat,</l>
          <l rend="indent5">when the busy<note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> kai viṉai mākkaḷ </term> gives which information: "people working with their hands" or, in a transferred sense "the busy people"?  </note> people complete [their] daily work.<note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> cey viṉai </term> is the work to be done, which presumably means "the work of the day"? </note></l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
